---
// About.astro: Sangeeth's Background & Development Philosophy
---

<section id="about" class="about-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">About Me</h2>
    
    <div class="about-grid">
      <!-- Story Card -->
      <div class="glass-card story-card">
        <h3>My Journey</h3>
        <p>
          I am a Software Engineer based in India who views coding as both an engineering discipline and a craft. Since finishing college, I have spent the past five years working on automation scripting, data-driven backends, and full-stack web applications.
        </p>
        <p>
          My passion lies in bridging the gap between raw backend scripting and delightful, human-centric interfaces. I strive to build software that is robust underneath, yet welcoming and simple on the surface.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of coding, I draw deep inspiration from hiking through green landscapes, exploring nature, and learning about clean, minimalist design frameworks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Philosophy / Approach -->
      <div class="glass-card philosophy-card">
        <h3>My Philosophy</h3>
        <ul class="value-list">
          <li>
            <div class="icon">☘️</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Simple Formats</strong>
              <p>I believe that anything can be achieved in a simple format. I actively avoid unnecessary complexity and over-engineered systems.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="icon">🍃</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Automation First</strong>
              <p>If a task is repetitive, it deserves a Python script. I value efficiency and creating tools that free up human creative energy.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="icon">✨</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Aesthetic Warmth</strong>
              <p>I like interfaces to feel alive, warm, and natural—using subtle animations, clean layouts, and rich color schemes.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about-section {
    background: transparent;
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-7);
  }

  .story-card h3, .philosophy-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--text-main);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent-glow);
    padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .story-card p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .story-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .value-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .value-list li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .value-list .icon {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
    width: 45px;
    height: 45px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 50%;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .value-list strong {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-main);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .value-list p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
